******
[2] Cholera - Nigeria (Kano, Zamfara States)
Date: Fri 10 Jan 2014
Source: The Windsor Star, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://www.windsorstar.com/health/Official+dead+2165+infected+cholera+epidemic+Nigerian+state/9372468/story.html


A Nigerian health official says a cholera epidemic has killed 71 people and infected 2165 since November 2013 in northern Kano state. Centre for Disease Control project director AbdulSalam Nasadi told reporters on Friday, 10 Jan 2014, that most cases are centered on Kano city, the country's 2nd largest [city].

Northern Zamfara state also has recorded hundreds of cholera cases. Nasadi said health officials have deployed to oversee cleanups and advise people on the need for cleanliness.

Lack of proper sanitation and clean water, pit toilets, mounds of uncollected garbage and storm drains blocked by garbage are among issues that contribute to health threats.

UN figures indicate half of Nigeria's more than 160 million people do not have safe water and 1/3rd do not have proper toilets.

