******
[3] Cholera - Congo DR (South Kivu Province)
Date: Wed 8 Jan 2014
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine transl., edited]
http://radiookapi.net/sante/2014/01/08/sud-kivu-80-cas-de-cholera-signales-sange/


The chief doctor of the area of health of the Ruzizi River (South Kivu Province), Delphin Babikire Byamungu, indicated Tuesday, 7 Jan 2014, that 80 cases of cholera, including 2 deaths, have been recorded in the city of Sange these last 8 days.

According to the physician, the drinking water is at the base of the rapid spread of this disease. "The flooded river impeded the functioning of the water supply system in this city. We are asking them to boil water before drinking," he said.

